title: For Sale:  1860 Colt Army
postcontent:
1860 Colt Army with Colt Letter of Authenticity. Serial number is 113112. The revolver is 100% original and is all matching, even the wedge! This has the New York address on the barrel. It is missing the wedge screw. Cartouches on the grips are present and legible. Navy scene is also visible. Patina is all original and well representative of the age of the piece. Rifeling is strong also. The hammer spring is faint but functions and locks. All 6 nipples are clear and complete. This is a great example of a barn find Colt.
The revolver has been lettered and shows it left Colt on April 23, 1863 and went to the Governor's Island Arsenal in New York.
